{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":true,"isActive":false,"flaws":{},"title":"Canvas Tutorial","mdn_url":"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial","locale":"de","native":"Deutsch","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\" title=\"HTML/Canvas\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://mdn.mozillademos.org/files/257/Canvas_tut_examples.jpg\" style=\"float: right;\" loading=\"lazy\"></a></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\" title=\"HTML/Canvas\"><strong><code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code></strong></a> (\"Leinwand\") ist ein <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML\" title=\"HTML\">HTML</a> Element, auf das man mit Hilfe von Skripten (normalerweise <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript\" title=\"JavaScript\">JavaScript</a>) Animationen, Grafiken oder Bilder projiziert. Die Bilder rechts zeigen Beispiele, die sich mit dem <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code>-Element erstellen lassen.</p>\n\n<p><code>Das &lt;canvas&gt;-</code>Element wurde zuerst&nbsp;von Apple für das Mac OS X Dashboard vorgestellt und später in Safari und Google Chrome implementiert. <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Gecko\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\" class=\"page-not-created\">Gecko</a> 1.8-basierte Browser&nbsp;wie Firefox 1.5 und jünger&nbsp;unterstützen dieses Element ebenfalls. Das <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code>-Element ist Teil der <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/\" rel=\" noopener\">WhatWG Web applications 1.0</a> Spezifikation (HTML5).</p>\n\n<p><span class=\"seoSummary\">Dieses Tutorial beschreibt die Grundlagen des Zeichnens von&nbsp;2d-Grafiken mit dem&nbsp;&lt;canvas&gt;-Element. Die Beispiele sollen die Möglichkeiten des Canvas aufzeigen. Der zugehörige Code dient als Einführung und kann als Vorlage für eigenen Content dienen.</span></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"before_you_start","title":"Vorbereitung","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Das <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code>-Element (\"Leinwand\") sinnvoll zu nutzen ist nicht schwierig, setzt aber ein einfaches Verständnis von <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/HTML\" title=\"HTML\">HTML</a> und <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/JavaScript\" title=\"JavaScript\">JavaScript</a> voraus. Einige ältere Browser unterstützen das <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code>-Element nicht. Die Standardgröße des Canvas beträgt 300 x 150 Pixel (Breite x Höhe). Selbstverständlich lassen diese sich über die Attribute <code>height</code> und <code>width</code> oder mit Hilfe von <a href=\"/de/docs/Web/CSS\" title=\"HTML\">CSS</a> ändern. Um auf dem <code>&lt;canvas&gt;</code>-Element zu zeichnen, nutzen Entwickler meist die&nbsp;JavaScript-Canvas-API \"on the fly\".</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"in_this_tutorial","title":"In diesem Tutorial","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Canvas_Tutorial/Grundlagen\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Basic_usage\">Grundlagen</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Canvas_Tutorial/Formen_zeichnen\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Drawing_shapes\">Formen zeichnen</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Using_images\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Using_images\">Bilder</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/de/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Applying_styles_and_colors\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Applying_styles_and_colors\">Stile und Farben verwenden</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Transformations\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Transformations\">Transformations</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Compositing\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Compositing\">Compositing</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Basic_animations\" title=\"Canvas_tutorial/Basic_animations\">Basic animations</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Optimizing_canvas\" title=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Guide/HTML/Canvas_tutorial/Optimizing_canvas\">Optimizing the canvas</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"Siehe auch","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API\" title=\"HTML/Canvas\">Canvas topic page</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial\" title=\"Drawing_Graphics_with_Canvas\">Drawing Graphics with Canvas</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/tag/Canvas_examples\" title=\"This is a link to an unwritten page\" class=\"page-not-created\">Canvas examples</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://html5tutorial.com\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5 Tutorial</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Drawing_text\" title=\"Drawing_text_using_a_canvas\">Drawing Text Using a Canvas</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"https://developer.apple.com/library/safari/#documentation/AudioVideo/Conceptual/HTML-canvas-guide/AddingText/AddingText.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40010542-CH6-SW4\" title=\"Adding Text to Canvas\" rel=\" noopener\">Adding Text to Canvas</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://canvimation.github.com/\" rel=\" noopener\">Canvas Drawing and Animation Application</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://billmill.org/static/canvastutorial/\" rel=\" noopener\">Interactive canvas tutorial</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://blog.nihilogic.dk/2009/02/html5-canvas-cheat-sheet.html\" rel=\" noopener\">Canvas Cheat Sheet with all attributes and methods</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://visitmix.com/labs/ai2canvas/\" rel=\" noopener\">Adobe Illustrator to Canvas plug-in</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"https://www.html5canvastutorials.com/\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5CanvasTutorials</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://html5tutorial.com/how-to-draw-n-grade-bezier-curve-with-canvas-api\" rel=\" noopener\">How to draw N grade Bézier curves with the Canvas API</a></li>\n <li><a class=\"external\" href=\"http://creativejs.com/2011/08/31-days-of-canvas-tutorials/\" rel=\" noopener\">31 days of canvas tutorials</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/2dcontext/\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">W3C Standard</a></li>\n <li><a href=\"http://www.tutorialspark.com/html5/HTML5_canvas_Intro.php\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">HTML5 Canvas tutorials and reference</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<div id=\"sect1\"><ul class=\"prev-next\">\n    \n    <li><a class=\"button minimal only-in-en-us\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Canvas_API/Tutorial/Basic_usage\" title=\"Currently only available in English (US)\">weiter  » (en-US)</a></li>\n</ul></div>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Vorbereitung","id":"before_you_start"},{"text":"In diesem Tutorial","id":"in_this_tutorial"},{"text":"Siehe auch","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"Dieses Tutorial beschreibt die Grundlagen des Zeichnens von 2d-Grafiken mit dem <canvas>-Element. Die Beispiele sollen die Möglichkeiten des Canvas aufzeigen. Der zugehörige Code dient als Einführung und kann als Vorlage für eigenen Content dienen.","popularity":0.0006,"modified":"2022-07-19T02:29:32.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Canvas tutorial","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)"},{"title":"Tutorial Canvas","locale":"es","native":"Español"},{"title":"Tutoriel canvas","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"Canvas チュートリアル","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"캔버스 튜토리얼","locale":"ko","native":"한국어"},{"title":"Rysowanie grafiki z elementem canvas","locale":"pl","native":"Polski"},{"title":"Canvas tutorial","locale":"pt-BR","native":"Português (do Brasil)"},{"title":"Руководство по Canvas","locale":"ru","native":"Русский"},{"title":"Canvas 教程","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"},{"title":"Canvas 教學文件","locale":"zh-TW","native":"正體中文 (繁體)"}],"source":{"folder":"de/web/api/canvas_api/tutorial","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/blob/main/files/de/web/api/canvas_api/tutorial/index.html","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/translated-content/commit/5fe4ab11259b37914fab4191